🌸 My swimwear collection with @vdmthelabel is now LIVE! We just dropped 
4 amazing new reversible prints and a textured reversible solid in lots of new styles all designed by me 🤗 Thank you to the VDM team for being so incredible to work with and trusting in your girl 🥲🥰♻️ Each set is made using 10 recycled plastic bottles from our oceans 🌎👙💘 #VDM video by @nickramirezx @celestebrightt @amandagonzxlez @nationwideproduction

node.text: Happy 4/20 everybody!!! I’m thrilled to have partnered up with my friends at @passthejeeter again for our second anual Cooking w/ Cindy - Baked Edition. With special guest @alexacollins . You cannot imagine how much fun we had making this video!! Hope you enjoy 🤗 Screenshot ingredients and instructions to recreate, and don’t forget to have a good time!! @passthejeeter 4/20 boxes available today all over CA. Thank you @alexacollins for joining me on this and everyone who worked behind the scenes to help create this amazing video!! @dayglowluk @luis_buron @ptracz

node.text:
———————————————————
Had so much fun teaming up with @passthejeeter to bring you this super tasty dessert you can enjoy today, and any day! Probably the most fun I’ve ever had in any of my cooking videos. ENJOY! (watch on IGTV for full size)

INSTRUCTION: (Disclaimer: in the video I use bigger portions because I had to make extra for gifting purposes. The ingredient list for you to use on the video serves 10-12) 
INSTRUCTIONS
1. Preheat oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit 
2. Cut your bread into 1-2” cubes and spread into an even layer on a baking sheet. Toast for 5 minutes.
3. In a large bowl, mash your bananas and then add the eggs, milk, condensed milk, brown sugar, pecans, chocolate chips, heavy cream, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt, and vanilla extract. Whisk until well mixed.
4. Stir in your cubed bread and mix well. Let it soak in there for about 20 minutes. 
5. Meanwhile, spray your 9x13” pan or muffin pan with non stick cooking spray. I use a muffin pan when I don’t have a lot of bread and only want single servings. You just fill each muffin pocket with the bread mixture and you’ll have muffin sized bread pudding. 
6. Once bread is soaked, fill into your pan. You can sprinkle top with remaining pecans. Bake for 1 hour for the 9x13 Pan and about 20 minutes for the Muffin Pan. Until center is no longer jiggly and it’s is lightly toasted on top. 
7. To make your caramel sauce, melt brown sugar in a small saucepan over medium heat. It will clump up at first, this is normal. Once fully melted, add butter and it will begin to bubble. Lower heat. Add vanilla and splash of milk and stir constantly until well mixed. 
8. Drizzle caramel over finished bread pudding. Slice and serve with a scoop of vanilla ice cream. ENJOY!

node.text:
I didn’t film the leg portion but I have a leg and booty video on my IGTV. Every time I do this in the morning I burn 700 calories in one hour. Puts me in a good mood and such a great start to my day. (Video is sped up so make sure you do ab movements slower with tight tummy)

Also, I keep getting DMs asking me where you can find my workout + cooking videos. They are all on my IGTV. You can get to my IGTV from my page, it’s the center icon above all my photos. Hope that helps! Thank you guys for the support and hope you’re having an incredible day 🤗

Workout gear (bands + gliders) are from @pvolve + bikini is @hannithebrand 💙

node.text:
The Prado Program is engineered to push you to become the best version of yourself, both mentally and physically. To me, fitness isn't just about how you look, it's about how you feel. It's about living a healthy, happy life, both physically and mentally. This isn't another influencer program thrown together with random workout videos. The Prado Program is designed by my coach, Luis Buron, aimed at building lean and muscular physiques for women.
Our program features step by step video training from me and Luis, coaching and motivating you every step along the way. Our nutrition and lifestyle coaching helps to build strong mental foundations to ensure your results last long term. Link in bio to sign up to email list and get notifications on our launch! LET’S BE WORKOUT BUDDIES!! @pradoprogram
